name: BlueToothDDS
tweet: 40) Let‚Äôs recap: Lots of moving pieces across the 3 subsegments of $FISV Payments & Network, but $3B+ of identified incremental revenue opportunities on a current base of < $6B would appear more than sufficient runway to support the 5-8% growth outlook for the combined unit ü§ó  https://t.co/BNrwYaA7ra

name: BlueToothDDS
tweet: 39) For this Digital Payments subsegment, $FISV is guiding to a 5-7% growth outlook, implying $100-120M/year of incremental revenue on a current base of ~$1.8B, which does not feel heroic given the tailwind of $1B+ of identified revenue opportunities from just 3 initiatives  https://t.co/V6lysa0KNu

name: BlueToothDDS
tweet: 38) With CheckFree Next, $FISV has incumbency you drive adoption: ~4,000 Bill Pay clients today including 24 of top 25 banks, 29M active Bill Pay users, network of 8,500 billers, access to ~60% of all eBills in US  FISV sizes this as a $350M+ incremental revenue opportunity  https://t.co/SVhIfZK0DQ

name: BlueToothDDS
tweet: 37) There are a number of pain points $FISV $MA $ACIW will solve with their respective next gen Bill Pay offerings: streamlined biller onboarding, smarter connectivity to billers, real-time payments leveraging new RTP rails, all from a consumer‚Äôs mobile banking app/wallet  https://t.co/O4QVD9zkmB

name: BlueToothDDS
tweet: 36) $FISV is dominant in bank Bill Pay (1.5+ of 2B bills paid in üá∫üá∏) and among the leaders in a fragmented market enabling Bill Pay directly with billers, with $ACIW $MA notable as well given their assets and aspirations in this space: up for grabs is $4-5T volume TAM in üá∫üá∏ alone

name: BlueToothDDS
tweet: 34) With the advent of real-time payments (RTP) in the üá∫üá∏, $FISV has enhanced TransferNow to enable instant fund transfers and mobile app/online banking integrations with banks/fintechs to drive growth +15-20% annually  FISV sizes this as a $150M incremental revenue opportunity  https://t.co/pt4a46Spf5

name: BlueToothDDS
tweet: 33) Already a large player enabling ACH, $FISV launched the TransferNow A2A interbank fund transfer platform, now an industry standard used by 7 of top 10 US banks to securely move $150B+/yr between the DDA and other internal or external accounts (e.g. MMA, brokerage, etc.)  https://t.co/JbIPxcT8dE

name: BlueToothDDS
tweet: 32) Overall Zelle continues to outpace Venmo with ~2x the P2P volumes  For $FISV, it‚Äôs Zelle volumes/usage are growing at 200%+ over the past 2 yrs (albeit off a low base)  As more banks onboard through FISV and these bank customers use Zelle, this is a $500M+ revenue opportunity  https://t.co/32vN4c4EuA

name: BlueToothDDS
tweet: 31) To date ~1,000 banks have signed up to use the Zelle network, but only ~730 are live today  Of this, 550 (75%) were onboarded by $FISV, the undisputed leader in Zelle enablement with hundreds more in the pipeline (including 2,000 on legacy PopMoney to eventually convert over)  https://t.co/0PHkinyw2u

name: BlueToothDDS
tweet: 30) Zelle is owned by EWS (itself owned by 7 large US banks) and only the big banks with sizable IT budgets have managed direct integration for P2P on the Zelle network  The long tail of 10,000+ small banks/credit unions are reliant on processors like $FISV to enable use of Zelle  https://t.co/M7Ichus69u

name: BlueToothDDS
